<p><img class="alignleft size-full wp-image-4381" style="margin: 10px;" title="Recommended Resource" src="http://energyandmotivation.com/wp-content/uploads/link_icon.gif" alt="link_icon" width="45" height="45" />I&#8217;ve just finished reading and commenting on article at the <strong>Abundance Tapestry</strong> blog, where you&#8217;ll find 10 tips on:</p>
<p><a title="Visit AbundanceTapestry.com " href="http://www.abundancetapestry.com/how-to-be-positive-all-the-time/">How to be Positive All the Time »</a></p>
<p>If you ask me, the most important skill you should develop (mentioned in the article) in order to stay positive almost all the time is the skill of <strong><em>awareness</em></strong>&#8230;</p>
<p><span id="more-5698"></span>When you&#8217;re constantly aware of your thoughts, emotions and actions you can be in control. You can change your perspective on things and you can constantly improve your thought patterns, your habits and what Tony Robbins calls your &#8220;Emotional Fitness&#8221;.</p>
<p>In my comment on the article I mention a technique I learned from one of Tony Robbin&#8217;s seminar recordings (that I&#8217;ve listened to several times). He calls it <strong>&#8220;turning frustration into fascination&#8221;</strong>. I use it a lot.</p>
<p>At first it feels a bit unnatural, but once you get the hang of it, you can automatically see obstacles, problems and failures in a sense of intense curiosity, like&#8230;</p>
<p><em>&#8220;wow, isn&#8217;t it interesting how it didn&#8217;t work&#8230; I wonder why this happened&#8230;&#8221;</em></p>
<p>instead of:</p>
<p><em>&#8220;damn, why isn&#8217;t it working for me?!&#8221;</em></p>
<p><em></em>I suggest that you try it a few times (and tell me how it worked for you&#8230;)</p>
